{{About|the term used to refer to Christmas trees|the tree itself|Christmas tree}}
{{POV|date=November 2017}}
{{unreferenced|date=November 2017}}
A '''holiday tree''' is a term generally used to describe a tree associated with the [[Christmas and holiday season]]. It became notable as a term used to refer to public tree lighting ceremonies in the United States, where the term [[Christmas tree]] was avoided due to concerns about [[separation of church and state]] and/or political correctness.

